data.CC: First Two Digits of Year Expressed in Format CCYY - The first two characters in the year CCYY
data.CD: Month and Year Expressed in Format MMMYYYY - Date expressed as Month, Month, Month, all upper case alpha and Year, Year, Year, Year e.g., JAN 1994, FEB 1994, etc
data.CQ: Date in Format CCYYQ - Date expressed as Year, Year, Year, Year, e.g., 1996, and Q as quarter within that year
data.DA: Range of Dates within a Single Month Expressed in Format DD-DD
data.DD: Day of Month in Numeric Format - The numeric day of the month expressed using a lead zero if the number of the day is less than ten
data.DT: Date and Time Expressed in Format CCYYMMDDHHMM
data.DTS: Range of Date and Time Expressed in Format CCYYMMDDHHMMSS-CCYYMMDDHHMMSS
data.EH: Last Digit of Year and Julian Date Expressed in Format YDDD
data.KA: Date Expressed in Format YYMMMDD - Date expressed as Year, Year, Month, Month, Month, Day, Day, e.g., 94JAN01
data.MD: Month of Year and Day of Month Expressed in Format MMDD
data.MM: Month of Year in Numeric Format - The month of the year consecutively numbered from one for January to twelve for December and expressed using a lead zero if the number of the month is less than ten
data.RD: Range of Dates Expressed in Format MMDDCCYY-MMDDCCYY
data.RD2: Range of Years Expressed in Format YY-YY
data.RD4: Range of Years Expressed in Format CCYY-CCYY
data.RD5: Range of Years and Months Expressed in Format CCYYMM-CCYYMM
data.RD6: Range of Dates Expressed in Format YYMMDD-YYMMDD
data.RD8: Range of Dates Expressed in Format CCYYMMDD-CCYYMMDD - A range of dates expressed in the format CCYYMMDD-CCYYMMDD where CCYY is the numerical expression of the century CC and year YY, MM is the numerical expression of the month within the year, and DD is the numerical expression of the day within the year; the first occurrence of CCYYMMDD is the beginning date and the second occurrence is the ending date
data.RDM: Range of Dates Expressed in Format YYMMDD-MMDD
data.RDT: Range of Date and Time, Expressed in Format CCYYMMDDHHMM-CCYYMMDDHHMM - A range of dates and times expressed in the format CCYYMMDDHHMM-CCYYMMDDHHMM where CCYY is the numerical expression of the century CC and year YY, MM is the numerical expression of the month within the year, DD is the numerical expression of the day within the month, HH is the numerical expression of hours in the day based on a twenty-four hour clock, and MM is the numerical expression of minutes within an hour; the first occurrence of CCYYMMDDHHMM is the starting time and the second is the ending time
data.RMD: Range of Months and Days Expressed in Format MMDD-MMDD
data.RMY: Range of Years and Months Expressed in Format YYMM-YYMM
data.RTM: Range of Time Expressed in Format HHMM-HHMM - A range of times expressed in the form HHMM-HHMM where HH is the numerical expression of hours in the day based on a twenty-four hour clock and MM is the numerical expression of minutes within an hour; the first occurrence of HHMM is the starting time and the second is the ending time
data.RTS: Date and Time Expressed in Format CCYYMMDDHHMMSS
data.TC: Julian Date Expressed in Format DDD
data.TM: Time Expressed in Format HHMM - Time expressed in the format HHMM where HH is the numerical expression of hours in the day based on a twenty-four hour clock and MM is the numerical expression of minutes within an hour
data.TR: Date and Time Expressed in Format DDMMYYHHMM
data.TS: Time Expressed in Format HHMMSS - Time expressed in the format HHMMSS where HH is the numerical expression of hours in the day based on a twenty-four hour clock, MM is the numerical expression of minutes within an hour, and SS is the numerical expression of seconds within a minute
data.YM: Year and Month Expressed in Format YYMM
data.YMM: Range of Year and Months, Expressed in CCYYMMM-MMM Format
data.YY: Last Two Digits of Year Expressed in Format CCYY - The year in the century (00 to 99)
